------------------------------- Mount Storage - PV and PVC ---------------------------------------------
An NFS-backend storage class is already configured.

Using details from this storage class, create a PersistentVolume(PV) with the following specifications:
Name: wev-pv
Access Mode: ReadOnlyMany
size: 1Gi
Reclaim Policy: same as the storage class
path is: /exports-ocp4/page


Next, create a PersistentVolumeClaim(PVC) with:
Name: web-pvc, Size: same as the PV (1Gi)
Access Mode: same as the PV (ReadOnlyMany)


Deploy the application with thease requirements:

it resides in a project named "webserver"
Deployment name: "web-landing"
Uses the image: registry.ocp4.example.com:8443/redhattraining/hello-world-nginx:v1.0

Mount path for Nginx: /usr/share/nginx/html
Replica count: 3

Accessible at: https:://exoplanets-declarative-manifests.apps.ocp4.example.com

url se dikh rha hai ye hostname hai : exoplanets-declarative-manifests.apps.ocp4.example.com


